  m_Name: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D3_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D3_L
  partName: Pes Distal Phalanx D3 Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left distal phalanx of the third hind digit supports the claw and forms the
    terminal skeletal component of the canine toe. This structure contributes significantly
    to traction, stability, and coordinated hindpaw movement during locomotion.
  - Tendons and ligaments attached to the bone enable controlled toe motion while
    maintaining balanced paw positioning during ground contact. The distal phalanx
    also protects soft tissues associated with the claw and assists with force distribution
    across the hindpaw.
